<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Well, EVERYTHING was red and there were NO rats or snakes around<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
Rats and Snakes are sort of &quot;shorthand&quot; for entry level creatures to kill. You are on the right path killing pawns, bats, wasps, etc. Bats and Wasps are the Rats and Snakes of that zone. Just be sure to cosider them as not EVERY bat will be blue to you. Never assume.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2. I learned to loot and sell to merchants...BUT they only bought my stuff once. No one will buy it now. I put everything in a bank and all of my slots are FULL now for equiptment. What am I supposed to do now?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
There are some things the mechants just <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>will not</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> buy (Orc heads, orc bones, wasp polen, etc.) If a merchant will not buy something, then assume it is a quest item (more on that in a bit). Feel free to keep perhaps one of each thing they won't buy and then be sure to go get thing that they will buy (bat wings, wasp wings, etc.) And remember, not every one standing around town is a merchant. There are guards, quest giving NPCs, and general townsfolk. Your best bet is to go into a store and click on the folks there. AND remember that you need to be close enough when you click on them, otherwise you just get the &quot;consider&quot; message (&quot;Merchant Bob judges you amiably.&quot;)<br>
<br>
On Quest items:<br>
You can go to the Allakazam website to look up quests and items. A list of quest items can be found here:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/dyn/quest_item_index.html">everquest.allakhazam.com/...index.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
So if you have wasp polen or an orc head (heck, even bone chips) you can look here to see if they are used for anything (look under &quot;W&quot; for wasp wings, &quot;B&quot; for bone chips, etc.)<br>
<br>
You can also look up quests in a particular zone or town by checking here:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/zlist.html">everquest.allakhazam.com/db/zlist.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
So if you ar ein Felwithe you can click there and see if any quests sound good to you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>3. HOW do I change clothes and get a ROBE. I have two rings, an earring, a cape, sleeves, a veil, a necklace, wrist and arm bands, etc. in my equipment. But I can not figure out how to get them to show up on my CHARACTER.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You should get a free robe when you start. If you take the note you initially got when you created your character and give it to your guild master (she is located in your guild hall).<br>
<br>
Here is a link to EQ Atlas, which has maps for EQ. This map of Felwithe...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/felwithe.html">www.eqatlas.com/felwithe.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
shows your guild hall is in Southern Felwithe (building #3). To get ther eyou go to room # 1 and go upstairs to the teleports. You walk into the Magicians port and you appear at the steps of your guild hall. Go in and on the left you will see some people in a room standing against the walls. There are the magician spell vendors. If you continue down the hall way you will see more rooms. Look for the person named in your note and give it to her. You will be rewarded with some experience and a robe (green I believe). <br>
<br>
Remember, this is not your typical RPG where every single item of clothing appears on your body. You won't see rings and medalions and whatnot. Heck, sometimes you won't even see pants. All that maters is what shows in your inventory screen.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>4. Also...what spells do I need (or SHOULD I look for) at this level.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, I told you above where the magician spell vendors are. At the Casters Realm you can get a list of Magician spells:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/spells/spells.asp?Class=Magician">eq.crgaming.com/spells/sp...s=Magician</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I would suggest the following spells in order of preference:<br>
1. Burst of Flame (important for attacking)<br>
2. Minor Shielding (for protection)<br>
---since you have a dagger and food and will always have them for the first 10 levels, forget the other level one spells for right now, you can get them later. Save your money for more important spells---<br>
<br>
When you get to level 4<br>
1. Upgrade to Burn (more damage)<br>
2. Elementalkin Earth (the best pet to start with and learn)<br>
3. Gate (to get around easier)<br>
<br>
The rest are up to you.<br>
<br>
And don't forget, to summon your Elementals you need malachite (a gem). One malachite for each pet summoned. You can buy them in bulk at the gem shop in southern Felwithe (bldg 5 on the S. Felwithe map)<br>
<br>
I hope this helps you out and gets you on your way. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
